"{\"uid\": \"rte.ie-sport-paris-2024-2024-0727-1462159-paris-2024-irish-in-action-of-day-2-of-olympic-games\", \"text\": \"We are very much up and running at the Paris Games, with plenty of Irish interest on Day 2.  The rowers get us going at 9.40am as Aifric Keogh and Fiona Murtagh compete in the women's pair heats. Paul O'Donovan and Fintan McCarthy begin their quest for a medal at 11.20am in Men's Lightweight Double Sculls heats.  In the middle of a busy morning of rowing action Mona McSharry enters the pool for the Women's 100m Breaststroke heats, which start at 10.27am.  At 10.32am Belfast boxer Aidan Walsh is in the ring to face Frenchman Makan Traore in the last 32 of the men's 71kg. Grainne Walsh and Jack Marley fight Anna Luca Hamori and Mateusz Bereznicki at 4.22pm and 7.32pm respectively.  There is a day of equestrian competition as the eventing team of Susie Berry (Wellfields Lincoln), Sarah Ennis (Action Lady M) and Austin O'Connor (Colorado Blue) are up.  The Ireland women's rugby sevens team gets started too with a couple of tough Pool B games against Great Britain and South Africa, while our sailors Robert Dickson and Sean Waddilove are on the water this afternoon.  You can follow the Olympic Games action all day with our live tracker on RT\\u00c9 Sport Online and the RT\\u00c9 News app, watch live from 9.15am-10.30pm on RT\\u00c92 and RT\\u00c9 Player, and listen to updates on RT\\u00c9 Radio 1 and 2fm.  (In order of start time)  1027-1043Women's 100m Breaststroke:Mona McSharry(Heat 5)  2010-2022Women's 100m Breaststroke semi-finals:Mona McSharry(if qualified)  1032Men's 71kg Rd 32: Makan Traore (Fra) vAidan Walsh (Irl)  1622Women's 66kg Rd 32:Grainne Walsh (Irl)v Anna Luca Hamori (Hun)  1932Men's 92kg Rd 16:Jack Marley (Irl)v Mateusz Bereznicki (Pol)  0930-1430Eventing - Team and Individual: Susie Berry (Wellfields Lincoln), Sarah Ennis (Action Lady M), Austin O'Connor (Colorado Blue)  0940Women's Pair heats: Aifric Keogh, Fiona Murtagh (Heat 2)  1000Men's Pair heats: Ross Corrigan, Nathan Timoney (Heat 1)  1030Women's Lightweight Double Sculls heats: Margaret Cremen, Aoife Casey (Heat 1)  1120Men's Lightweight Double Sculls: Paul O'Donovan, Fintan McCarthy (Heat 3)  1140Women's Four heats: Emily Hegarty, Natalie Long, Eimear Lambe, Imogen Magner (Heat 2)  Women's Pool Phase - Pool B:  1430Ireland v Great Britain  1800Ireland v South Africa  Skiff Races 1-3 (1440-1520, 1532-1612, 1624-1704): Robert Dickson, Sean Waddilove  Watch the 2024 Olympic Games with 14 hours of televised action on RT\\u00c92 and RT\\u00c9 Player each day. Listen to extensive radio coverage on RT\\u00c9 Radio 1 and 2fm's Game On and follow each moment from Paris on RT\\u00c9.ie, the RT\\u00c9 News app and all RT\\u00c9 digital platforms. Listen to the daily RT\\u00c9 Sport Olympics Podcast.  \\u00a9 RT\\u00c9 2026. RT\\u00c9.ie is the website of Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann, Ireland's National Public Service Media. RT\\u00c9 is not responsible for the content of external internet sites.  Images Courtesy of Getty Images.\"}"